% Standard ctx.obj parameters available in PDD CLI commands:
%
% The Click context object (`ctx.obj`) is a dictionary populated by the main CLI group
% with the following keys:
%   - 'verbose' (bool): Enable verbose output for debugging.
%   - 'strength' (float): LLM generation strength parameter.
%   - 'temperature' (float): LLM temperature parameter.
%   - 'time' (float | None): Relative thinking time in [0.0â€“1.0], or None if not set.
%   - 'force' (bool): Overwrite existing output files without prompting.
%   - 'quiet' (bool): Suppress non-essential output.
%   - 'local' (bool): Use local execution instead of cloud execution.
%   - 'context' (str | None): Optional context directory override.
%   - 'confirm_callback' (Callable | None): Optional TUI confirmation callback.
%   - 'local' (bool): Force local execution instead of cloud.
%
% When a cmd_* function accepts optional `strength` and `temperature` parameters directly,
% the resolution pattern is: use the function parameter if not None, otherwise fall back
% to ctx.obj["strength"] or ctx.obj["temperature"]. This allows orchestrators to pass
% explicit values that override the CLI context.
